---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Use Cases | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>Use Cases</h1>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is designed first for regulated financial workflows where probabilistic model behavior cannot serve as the authorization
      boundary. It helps teams govern whether AI-assisted actions are allowed to proceed under policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Priority financial workflows</h2>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>AI-assisted payment dispute handling</h3>
        <p>Request scope, case context, and action eligibility must be policy-gated before AI-assisted work is allowed to proceed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Exception operations</h3>
        <p>AI may summarize or recommend, but deterministic policy control must govern whether execution-related steps are allowed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Analyst and servicing workflows</h3>
        <p>Regulated data access and action paths require explicit, reviewable controls before AI interaction is allowed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operational patterns</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Policy-gated requests before model execution</li>
      <li>Deterministic allow/deny at the request boundary</li>
      <li>Explicit reviewable evidence for governed workflows</li>
      <li>Fail-closed handling when required policy or trust conditions are not met</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Financial workflow focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is focused first on financial-services workflows where authorization, evidence, and control ownership remain explicit. It is
      not being presented here as a broad multi-industry platform page.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Explore by outcome</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/platform">Understand platform coverage</a></li>
      <li><a href="/trust-assurance">Review assurance model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/deployment">Compare deployment posture</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/design-partner-program">Request governance review support</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Start a platform discussion</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
